WEBVTT

00:13.847 --> 00:18.184
I've met plenty of people who turned out
to be nice once I talked to them.

00:18.768 --> 00:21.688
People often said I was hard to approach.

00:24.774 --> 00:27.986
I'm terrible at starting conversations.

00:28.069 --> 00:30.196
I'm glad we can talk about manga together.

00:33.283 --> 00:37.704
It's been boring
because there's no one I click with.

00:41.332 --> 00:42.584
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

00:43.084 --> 00:45.795
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Thank you. Thank you.

00:46.629 --> 00:47.756
Don't mention it.

00:49.424 --> 00:53.553
If the environment is partly to blame
for the isolation,

00:54.637 --> 00:56.014
I would...

00:57.557 --> 00:58.558
HAMBURGER BOM BOM

00:58.641 --> 00:59.809
Yeah. Then, this guy...

00:59.893 --> 01:02.228
Amamiya? You listening?

01:03.521 --> 01:04.689
'Course I am.

01:05.440 --> 01:06.941
Oh, well.

02:38.533 --> 02:42.954
EPISODE 2
LOCKSMITH

02:43.538 --> 02:45.081
Join us for a good time.

02:45.165 --> 02:46.207
No, thanks!

02:46.833 --> 02:47.834
What do I even do?

02:47.917 --> 02:49.252
TWO AGAINST ONE
WHAT IF I UPSET THEM

02:49.335 --> 02:50.336
I'm terrified and angry.

02:50.420 --> 02:51.713
THEY'RE MOCKING ME
WHAT A WASTE OF TIME

02:52.297 --> 02:53.715
- How frustrating.
- Let's go.

02:53.798 --> 02:55.008
- Come with us.
- It's gonna be fun.

02:55.091 --> 02:57.802
I said I'm not interested!

02:59.053 --> 03:01.806
I'm serious. Leave me alone.

03:04.809 --> 03:05.852
Bye.

03:08.313 --> 03:09.898
Sorry. You okay?

03:11.983 --> 03:13.234
I thought it was you.

03:14.777 --> 03:16.070
Mr. Giraffe?

03:16.821 --> 03:18.239
I HAVE TO TAKE THE CROSSWALK
OVER THERE TO GET TO THIS SIDE

03:18.323 --> 03:19.657
Sorry I ignored you back there.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.245
Please pretend like we're friends.

03:24.329 --> 03:25.830
I'm sorry,

03:25.914 --> 03:28.833
but please stay with me
until we're out of their sight.

03:29.334 --> 03:30.335
Say what?

03:30.835 --> 03:34.672
I was able to meet up with a friend,
so I'm okay now. Bye!

03:34.756 --> 03:35.757
What?

03:36.966 --> 03:39.385
BLURRY

03:40.428 --> 03:42.138
Does she know them?

03:42.222 --> 03:44.390
Maybe not.

03:45.975 --> 03:47.185
SCURRYING AWAY

03:47.268 --> 03:49.062
High schoolers these days are scary.

03:49.145 --> 03:50.146
Ain't that right.

03:52.732 --> 03:54.400
Thank you so much.

03:54.984 --> 03:57.904
Huh? I didn't do anything, did I?

03:57.987 --> 04:00.156
Didn't you know them?

04:01.783 --> 04:03.743
They came up to me out of nowhere.

04:04.827 --> 04:06.246
You're so popular.

04:06.746 --> 04:08.414
- It's not like that.
- What?

04:10.208 --> 04:11.376
I mean,

04:11.876 --> 04:14.754
what you saw wasn't like that.

04:15.797 --> 04:20.176
Their vibe was that nothing else mattered
as long as they were having a good time.

04:21.052 --> 04:23.513
Rather, they were looking down on me,

04:23.596 --> 04:26.933
so it's not a situation
I can be happy about. So...

04:30.311 --> 04:33.022
Hold on, why am I defending myself?

04:33.106 --> 04:35.316
I should just play it off.

04:36.442 --> 04:37.694
He's gonna get weirded out.

04:40.238 --> 04:42.991
Should I have punched them?

04:43.783 --> 04:46.244
No, you don't need to take it that far.

04:46.327 --> 04:47.704
Are you sure?

04:48.413 --> 04:52.417
Actually, I'm sorry. It's like
I used you to get away from them.

04:52.917 --> 04:55.712
Why are you apologizing?
It's totally fine.

04:55.795 --> 04:58.840
I wouldn't get upset
over something like this.

05:01.426 --> 05:03.261
Do you live around here, Himuro?

05:03.761 --> 05:05.888
No. I wanted to go
to the community center.

05:05.972 --> 05:08.099
What? That's where I was going too.

05:08.182 --> 05:10.101
Then, why don't we walk together?

05:20.194 --> 05:23.906
Extracurricular activities will be on hold
during the exam preparation period...

05:23.990 --> 05:26.701
- HR is going on forever!
- ...so your daily routine may be disrupted.

05:26.784 --> 05:29.871
Koyun, sorry I'm making you wait!

05:31.372 --> 05:32.874
Say...

05:37.086 --> 05:39.547
I'd like to know your name, please.

05:39.630 --> 05:42.842
Right. I never told you my name.

05:42.925 --> 05:43.968
My bad.

05:45.136 --> 05:47.513
You can just call me Yota.

05:47.597 --> 05:49.682
He only gave me his first name.

05:49.766 --> 05:50.767
I WANTED TO KNOW HIS LAST NAME

05:50.850 --> 05:52.769
It's a pleasure to meet you, Himuro.

05:54.145 --> 05:55.271
Sorry.

05:55.354 --> 05:58.858
My last name's actually Hikawa,
not Himuro.

05:58.941 --> 06:00.818
No way! Sorry.

06:00.902 --> 06:02.779
You should've told me sooner.

06:07.075 --> 06:10.286
How much longer is it to get
to the community center?

06:10.369 --> 06:12.205
I'm terrible with maps.

06:12.288 --> 06:14.373
We'll be there in about five minutes.

06:15.208 --> 06:16.292
Five minutes.

06:17.251 --> 06:19.462
Can we keep
the conversation going for that long?

06:24.759 --> 06:27.804
Hikawa, are you good friends with Miki?

06:28.721 --> 06:31.599
We're childhood friends.

06:31.682 --> 06:34.185
We live close, and we went to the same
elementary and middle school.

06:34.268 --> 06:36.062
Is that so?

06:37.063 --> 06:40.483
We went to the same cram school
in middle school.

06:40.566 --> 06:41.567
What?

06:42.568 --> 06:44.195
They've been friends since middle school?

06:44.278 --> 06:47.448
Does that mean he knows the real Miki?

06:47.532 --> 06:49.117
Now Miki.

06:49.200 --> 06:50.243
You know, Miki,

06:50.827 --> 06:53.704
I liked her much better
the way she used to be.

06:54.288 --> 06:55.540
Me too.

06:55.623 --> 06:56.624
Right?

06:56.707 --> 06:59.168
Honestly, I want to tell everyone
what she's really like.

06:59.252 --> 07:01.379
Seriously, what a waste.

07:02.922 --> 07:04.590
No matter what you're like,

07:04.674 --> 07:07.093
some people will want to stick by you.

07:11.097 --> 07:12.181
You've gotta be kidding.

07:13.266 --> 07:15.268
Hold on, isn't that Yota?

07:16.853 --> 07:17.937
You're right.

07:18.020 --> 07:20.356
But wait. That girl next to him, she's...

07:22.275 --> 07:23.609
What?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.611
MEITEN COMMUNITY CENTER

07:30.199 --> 07:31.742
Here's your seat, Miki.

07:31.826 --> 07:32.910
Thanks.

07:32.994 --> 07:36.247
What the... What kind of pairing is this?

07:37.081 --> 07:38.291
What kind...

07:38.374 --> 07:39.584
Great question.

07:42.503 --> 07:43.504
What?

07:44.172 --> 07:46.132
Hey, I'm the one asking.

07:50.553 --> 07:51.762
Sorry.

07:53.848 --> 07:56.559
Geez! You guys surprised me!

07:56.642 --> 07:59.020
Why didn't you give me a heads up?

07:59.103 --> 08:01.355
I told her not to say anything.

08:01.439 --> 08:02.857
I told her, "Let's surprise Miki!"

08:02.940 --> 08:05.693
You too, Koyun.
Why'd you go along with it?

08:06.611 --> 08:10.573
More importantly,
didn't you punch the jerks who hit on her?

08:11.157 --> 08:13.284
No. Hikawa didn't want me to.

08:13.993 --> 08:16.037
There's no need to go that far.

08:16.120 --> 08:17.163
What?

08:18.289 --> 08:21.375
Are you taking the same train?
I'll walk you to the station.

08:21.459 --> 08:22.835
Thanks!

08:24.295 --> 08:26.589
Yota, do you go to that study room often?

08:26.672 --> 08:28.257
Yeah.

08:28.799 --> 08:31.302
My younger brother and sister
are still little.

08:31.385 --> 08:33.346
It's too noisy at home.

08:33.429 --> 08:35.973
Right. How old are they again?

08:36.057 --> 08:38.518
They're both three years old.
They're twins.

08:39.060 --> 08:40.144
HIS MOM IS SUCH A TROOPER...

08:40.228 --> 08:41.729
That's quite an age gap.

08:42.313 --> 08:44.941
It's partly because
of the toddlers at home,

08:45.024 --> 08:47.235
but I can focus better at the study room.

08:47.318 --> 08:50.613
I feel you. I didn't check my phone today!

08:50.696 --> 08:52.907
I didn't even have space to fool around.

08:52.990 --> 08:54.492
Don't fool around.

08:56.577 --> 08:58.496
Give me a minute.

08:58.579 --> 09:02.250
I need some sugar to recharge
after all the studying I did.

09:03.251 --> 09:05.253
Great idea. I'll grab a drink too.

09:12.218 --> 09:14.303
He's taller than the vending machine.

09:14.387 --> 09:15.513
It must be nice.

09:16.931 --> 09:19.267
I wish I was born that way.

09:19.850 --> 09:21.394
Take your pick, you two.

09:21.477 --> 09:22.645
You don't mind?

09:22.728 --> 09:24.397
I know you want the red bean soup, Miki.

09:24.480 --> 09:26.148
You know me well.

09:26.232 --> 09:28.025
Thanks, Yota.

09:28.109 --> 09:30.152
I'll cover you next time.

09:31.320 --> 09:32.655
Oh, my gosh! Why?

09:33.406 --> 09:37.577
You used a bill, so how'd you
manage to scatter coins everywhere?

09:37.660 --> 09:39.412
My bad.

09:40.329 --> 09:42.331
What do you want to drink, Hikawa?

09:42.415 --> 09:43.666
Me?

09:43.749 --> 09:45.001
I FEEL BAD - SHAKE SHAKE

09:45.084 --> 09:46.294
I...

09:47.712 --> 09:50.214
Here, Miki. You can pick for her.

09:50.298 --> 09:51.507
Leave it to me.

09:52.008 --> 09:55.094
How about a warm corn soup for Koyun?

09:55.177 --> 09:58.556
But I'm craving red bean soup,
so red bean soup it is!

09:58.639 --> 10:00.182
What the heck?

10:00.266 --> 10:04.520
Well, I want her to drink the same thing
so we can both say it's tasty.

10:05.646 --> 10:06.814
You're so selfish.

10:08.107 --> 10:09.567
They really do get along.

10:10.234 --> 10:11.569
RED BEAN SOUP

10:13.321 --> 10:17.992
Like I said earlier,
we went to the same cram school.

10:18.075 --> 10:21.078
Miki, Minato, and I were always together.

10:21.162 --> 10:24.248
Oh, yeah. We used to
eat and talk after cram school.

10:24.749 --> 10:27.752
Mina... You mean Amamiya.

10:27.835 --> 10:30.087
Hold on, Koyun, you know Minato too?

10:30.671 --> 10:33.090
No, not really.

10:33.174 --> 10:34.967
STRETCH

10:35.676 --> 10:38.137
Don't tell me he picked on you again.

10:38.220 --> 10:39.221
Again?

10:41.182 --> 10:43.100
You poor thing.

10:43.184 --> 10:45.311
You can just ignore him.

10:45.394 --> 10:48.606
Yota, do you not get along with Amamiya?

10:49.649 --> 10:51.484
I'm just kidding.

10:53.319 --> 10:55.696
Koyun, Yota and Minato.

10:56.197 --> 10:59.867
Hikawa, do people around you
call you Koyun?

10:59.950 --> 11:00.951
PEOPLE RARELY CALL HER BY NAME

11:01.035 --> 11:02.244
No, only Miki does.

11:02.328 --> 11:04.038
- Koyun.
- Yes?

11:04.121 --> 11:05.998
It's a good nickname.

11:06.082 --> 11:07.375
Right?

11:07.458 --> 11:09.001
Why are you smug about it?

11:09.710 --> 11:12.880
I told you, you can be casual with me.

11:12.963 --> 11:15.049
I don't like people being overly formal.

11:15.132 --> 11:16.926
- No more talking so politely.
- What?

11:17.009 --> 11:18.135
I get it.

11:18.219 --> 11:21.013
I also feel more comfortable
when people are casual.

11:21.097 --> 11:22.973
Is that how it is?

11:24.141 --> 11:25.476
Thank you!

11:26.102 --> 11:28.270
Yota, will you be
at the study room tomorrow too?

11:28.354 --> 11:30.106
Yeah. I'll be there.

11:30.189 --> 11:31.524
Then, see you tomorrow.

11:32.149 --> 11:33.359
See you tomorrow.

11:35.444 --> 11:36.654
'Til tomorrow.

11:52.711 --> 11:55.339
Koyuki Hikawa.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.845
Huh, was there a girl like that?

12:00.928 --> 12:03.681
I think she's Hikawa from Class 2.

12:04.432 --> 12:06.767
Word is, she's always grouchy
and doesn't fit in with her class.

12:13.315 --> 12:16.277
I thought Class 2 was pretty quiet.

12:17.153 --> 12:21.240
Maybe it's more that she can't find
anyone she can relate to.

12:22.658 --> 12:26.745
Since then, I kept following her
with my eyes every time we crossed paths.

12:27.746 --> 12:28.831
She's by herself again.

12:31.959 --> 12:33.085
STRETCH

12:33.836 --> 12:35.379
I always thought,

12:36.547 --> 12:39.383
"What a p..."

12:40.426 --> 12:42.178
INCOMING CALL
NINE AUDIO

12:44.180 --> 12:46.015
Sorry, Minato.

12:46.098 --> 12:47.641
Can we meet right now?

12:47.725 --> 12:49.101
There's something I want to talk about.

12:50.186 --> 12:51.979
Okay. I'll come out.

13:08.787 --> 13:10.247
What's this out of the blue?

13:14.418 --> 13:15.461
You must be cold.

13:20.299 --> 13:21.967
ROYAL MILK TEA

13:22.051 --> 13:23.219
I want to break up.

13:27.932 --> 13:29.225
What makes you say that?

13:32.186 --> 13:33.729
I can't trust you.

13:35.064 --> 13:38.234
You could chalk it up to kindness,

13:39.318 --> 13:44.240
but you never liked me to begin with,
did you, Minato?

13:45.157 --> 13:48.619
I can tell you're not into me.

13:48.702 --> 13:52.456
Did I do something
that made you feel lonely?

13:53.958 --> 13:56.877
Don't respond
to everything with questions.

13:56.961 --> 14:01.006
You always do that.
I want to know how you really feel.

14:07.012 --> 14:08.347
You know what, Minato?

14:09.348 --> 14:12.059
You really don't have a sense of self.

14:15.020 --> 14:16.272
I'm home.

14:17.856 --> 14:21.569
Were you out, Minato?
Was it something urgent?

14:22.278 --> 14:23.279
No.

14:23.946 --> 14:25.531
It was nothing, really.

14:30.369 --> 14:32.997
It's gonna be fine, Amamiya.
It must be rough.

14:33.080 --> 14:35.499
Hey, I just got dumped.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.042
Why don't you comfort me a little?

14:37.126 --> 14:38.419
Well, how many times is it now?

14:38.502 --> 14:40.129
It's starting to be funny.

14:40.212 --> 14:43.215
Though, I'm sure you'll have
a new girlfriend in no time. Darn it, you!

14:43.299 --> 14:46.135
Amamiya, you broke up? Again?

14:46.218 --> 14:47.219
Yup.

14:47.803 --> 14:52.600
She called me out when I was studying
last night. Then she broke up with me.

14:52.683 --> 14:53.851
That's rough.

14:53.934 --> 14:57.229
For some reason, I always get dumped.

14:58.898 --> 15:00.232
Why do you think that is?

15:01.942 --> 15:03.694
WE LET OUR GUARD DOWN,
AND THIS AGAIN - THUMP THUMP

15:03.777 --> 15:05.029
Fujita! Don't let him trick you.

15:05.112 --> 15:06.947
Don't hold eye contact
for longer than three seconds!

15:07.031 --> 15:08.365
Okay.

15:08.449 --> 15:11.243
- I'll hold him down. Now, go!
- Morning... Huh?

15:11.327 --> 15:14.914
Minato, what'd you do this time? Sheesh.

15:14.997 --> 15:18.000
I haven't done a thing. Why do you
always assume I've done something wrong?

15:19.293 --> 15:21.253
Speaking of...

15:27.843 --> 15:30.971
The cafeteria has a lot more options
if you get there early.

15:31.513 --> 15:33.140
- Hey, Yota.
- Yeah?

15:33.724 --> 15:36.644
Weren't you walking home
with Hikawa yesterday?

15:37.227 --> 15:38.646
I'm sure he'd say...

15:38.729 --> 15:41.982
It's not like that!
It's a misunderstanding!

15:42.983 --> 15:44.401
You saw us.

15:44.485 --> 15:45.527
What?

15:46.278 --> 15:49.281
We happened to run into each other,
then decided to walk together.

15:52.618 --> 15:55.829
Of course, yeah.

15:55.913 --> 15:57.289
After all, you're...

16:01.126 --> 16:03.545
NURSE'S OFFICE

16:04.129 --> 16:06.090
Hey, Hikawa. Hello.

16:06.173 --> 16:08.050
Why are you at the nurse's office?
Are you hurt?

16:08.133 --> 16:10.678
No.

16:11.595 --> 16:12.930
What's going on?

16:14.181 --> 16:15.182
Yota.

16:16.141 --> 16:17.434
"Yota"?

16:17.518 --> 16:19.311
Koyun.

16:20.312 --> 16:21.313
"Koyun"?

16:21.397 --> 16:23.816
Are you feeling sick? Are you okay?

16:23.899 --> 16:26.819
I just came to warm up by the heater.

16:26.902 --> 16:29.738
What? Is it even that cold today?

16:29.822 --> 16:31.824
It is, actually.
It's down to nine degrees Celsius.

16:31.907 --> 16:33.117
You're wearing your contacts today?

16:33.200 --> 16:35.828
- She won't even glance at me.
- Yup, totally. Wanna look at them?

16:35.911 --> 16:37.830
- Not really.
- Hey, Hikawa.

16:37.913 --> 16:38.914
SCHOOL NURSE - NORIKO

16:38.998 --> 16:42.251
You're letting the cold air in.
If you're done, then leave.

16:42.334 --> 16:43.335
Shoo, shoo.

16:44.795 --> 16:46.880
We got in trouble.

16:46.964 --> 16:48.757
Noriko's always like that.

16:48.841 --> 16:51.719
Is your next class on the fourth floor?

16:51.802 --> 16:53.721
We're going upstairs too.

16:53.804 --> 16:55.347
No...

16:56.056 --> 16:59.226
I meant to stop by my locker.
It's on the first floor.

16:59.977 --> 17:00.978
Okay.

17:01.061 --> 17:02.146
Well, then...

17:02.229 --> 17:03.230
SCUTTLING AWAY

17:03.313 --> 17:04.773
See you later.

17:06.108 --> 17:07.317
"See you later"?

17:16.160 --> 17:18.912
They happened
to run into each other, right?

17:22.708 --> 17:26.170
Another productive night down!

17:26.837 --> 17:29.506
But there are still concepts
I'm not quite grasping.

17:29.590 --> 17:32.384
Sometimes, I want to talk while studying.

17:32.968 --> 17:35.888
What if we study together in my classroom
after school tomorrow?

17:35.971 --> 17:37.556
I'll help you with what I can.

17:37.639 --> 17:38.932
Are you sure?

17:39.016 --> 17:42.019
I'm counting on you, Yota-sensei!

17:42.102 --> 17:43.645
It's no biggie--

17:44.980 --> 17:46.857
Sensei! I heard a loud thud!

17:46.940 --> 17:48.025
Ouch.

17:48.525 --> 17:50.652
Hey! Does your head hurt?

17:50.736 --> 17:53.447
Well, I'm always bumping
my head into things.

17:55.282 --> 17:57.284
Yota's classroom...

17:58.619 --> 18:00.287
seems noisy.

18:01.455 --> 18:03.040
- It'll be fine.
- What?

18:03.123 --> 18:05.834
The rambunctious ones
take off as soon as the bell rings.

18:05.918 --> 18:07.169
True that.

18:07.252 --> 18:09.463
- He read my mind. I'm embarrassed.
- Koyun's not good with that kinda vibe.

18:09.546 --> 18:11.173
I'M ALL FOR IT THOUGH
CHUCKLE

18:13.759 --> 18:15.928
SEAT FOR ONE

18:19.765 --> 18:22.684
Rock, paper, scissors.

18:24.353 --> 18:25.395
Please, go ahead.

18:26.146 --> 18:27.606
You can take the seat.

18:27.689 --> 18:28.816
PUBLIC FACE

18:28.899 --> 18:31.276
Don't mind us.
We're getting off at the next stop.

18:31.360 --> 18:32.361
What?

18:33.737 --> 18:37.116
Please use the stairs in the center
of the platform to transfer between lines.

18:39.201 --> 18:41.995
- The doors on platform three are closing.
- Quick! Shoot, shoot!

18:45.082 --> 18:46.959
We made it.

18:48.585 --> 18:52.131
Why'd you lie? Just give him the seat.

18:52.214 --> 18:54.758
I got embarrassed.

18:54.842 --> 18:56.760
FOGGY

18:56.844 --> 19:00.639
Shoot, the glass fogs up
when I get close to it.

19:07.104 --> 19:09.022
Now I'm laughing too.

19:13.068 --> 19:15.946
Once the exams are over,
I'm signing up for more shifts at work.

19:16.029 --> 19:18.866
We won't be able to go home together,
but stop by my restaurant sometime, Koyun.

19:18.949 --> 19:20.784
THEY TEND TO TALK A LITTLE MORE
BEFORE THEY SAY GOODBYE

19:20.868 --> 19:24.538
You've never been before.
I'll give you an extra serving of smiles.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.418
Stylish burger!

19:29.501 --> 19:32.296
It's kinda intimidating
to eat there by myself.

19:32.379 --> 19:33.422
I'M A HIGH SCHOOLER

19:33.505 --> 19:35.883
Spending over 1,000 yen on a burger
takes some nerve.

19:35.966 --> 19:38.343
I'll talk to the manager,
he'll hook you up with a discount.

19:38.427 --> 19:40.262
I've got you covered.

19:40.345 --> 19:41.555
MANAGER

19:42.139 --> 19:44.600
If you don't want to come alone,
just bring Yota.

19:45.684 --> 19:47.561
He's got his club activities.

19:51.940 --> 19:53.066
See ya.

19:53.650 --> 19:54.860
See you tomorrow.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.548
The laundry.

20:28.560 --> 20:31.521
Was I smiling?

20:35.651 --> 20:37.486
Today was so much fun.

20:37.569 --> 20:41.114
I can't help but feel giddy
about what tomorrow might bring.

20:43.075 --> 20:44.493
I'm better off on my own.

20:44.576 --> 20:45.744
This is fun.

20:45.827 --> 20:47.246
I'd rather not get involved.

20:47.329 --> 20:48.622
I want to talk to them again.

20:48.705 --> 20:50.249
Why can't they leave me alone?

20:50.332 --> 20:51.625
I'm looking forward to tomorrow.

20:54.086 --> 20:57.631
No part of me is fake, but...

20:58.131 --> 20:59.341
they contradict each other.

21:00.968 --> 21:04.012
What do I really want to do?

21:06.223 --> 21:08.767
I don't understand my own feelings.

21:13.105 --> 21:15.023
GRADE 1 CLASS 6

21:15.107 --> 21:16.608
Sneaking in.

21:17.609 --> 21:20.028
Koyun! Come on in.

21:20.654 --> 21:21.905
Pardon me.

21:24.992 --> 21:27.119
Miki says she's running late.

21:27.869 --> 21:29.997
She pinged me too.

21:30.664 --> 21:33.083
Class 5 has the tendency to drag out HR.

21:34.126 --> 21:36.336
Why don't we make a group chat?

21:37.212 --> 21:38.213
Good idea.

21:39.631 --> 21:40.882
Minato.

21:41.550 --> 21:45.178
Are you two dating?

21:45.804 --> 21:47.431
No. You've got the wrong idea.

21:47.514 --> 21:49.474
Miki will be joining us shortly.

21:49.975 --> 21:52.602
Miki? What's up with your friend group?

21:52.686 --> 21:53.687
RATTLE

21:54.730 --> 21:56.189
Minato, why are you here?

21:56.273 --> 21:58.317
What, am I not supposed to be?

21:58.817 --> 22:00.527
Not at all.

22:01.528 --> 22:03.280
Miki is being herself.

22:03.780 --> 22:05.449
FUNDAMENTALS OF PHYSICS

22:05.532 --> 22:08.118
What's this? Is this a study group?

22:08.201 --> 22:09.202
Bingo.

22:16.043 --> 22:17.044
How fun.

22:17.544 --> 22:19.171
Let me join too.

22:23.216 --> 22:24.217
What?

23:50.262 --> 23:55.267
Subtitle translation by: Megumi Hunter
